				<td colspan="2"><span>Keiz's method works for those who get to 60 and find themselves with a pathetically low defense.
<br />

<br />
Really, playing a bard is all about finding the balance.  If you group exclusively, your player skills will not be as well-honed as they could be.  While I don't solo much anymore, the skills involved made me a better player.  Conversely, one who kites all the time will miss out on a lot of critical player and character skills.
<br />

<br />
Get the Yin and the Yang of being a bard, and you will be enlightened both in your character and in your own ability.</span></td>
