			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Doh! so they've nerfed her have they? makes sense, but a pity.
<br />
Ok, next trick.
<br />
Second floor of Tofs (once again, think it's second floor).  You zone into level, there's a chamber you're in right to left.  Ahead an entrance into a fairly large room. Follow the room round to the right and near a bookcase, there's a little raised platform.  As a trap, it cons blue to you, causes a teeny bit of damage that can be out regenned, and gives skills up to defense.
<br />
Take longer than the Erudin place as you can't leave it overnight.  There's nothing that paths close, but each bit of damage gradually pushes you off the platform so you have to keep running back onto it again.  (Also seem to recall it occasionally inturupted singing to).  Used this trap a fair while ago, and skill ups where very slow, max stats as best can before visiting.  After an hour and 3 skillups got bored and wandered off. It was later I heard of the Erudin defence trainer and used that to finish off.  
<br />
It's also a pain to get to second floor, you've got to get the keys, so it isn't a 10 minute thing when you log in or just before you log off.
<br />
Hope this helps,
<br />
Jyve</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
