				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Defense skills<a name="33300"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 7 04 8:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Koka, everything in your post except the low defense part is in agreement with my statement.  I am full of sh*t because I state facts?  If you group at least 1/3d of every level, ALL your combat skills should be maxed.
<br />

<br />
Swarming is bad if that is all you do.  A 65 Bard who rarely grouped on the way up is going to find him or herself lacking not only skills as per the toon's stats, but also skills as far as what to do in a group, what to sing to be effective.  A lot of times they will be underequipped as well, although that is not a huge deal.
<br />

<br />
You said you solod, raided and group.  That is great, but I dont understand why your defensive skills are so low.  There is really no reason for it unless you mainly solo or raid.  Raiding, your defensive skills shouldnt raise much anyway, unless for you are the MT ;o).  Soloing, there is no way to raise defensive skills really, unless you have a cleric bot.  Grouping is really the only way to get em up.  Unless you use some trick, exploit, or non fun way of raising them. 
<br />
I solo once in a while myself, and raid, and group.  I did so on my way up as well.  When I got to 65, I didnt have to ask for cheats or tricks on how to raise skills I ignored.  To be honest, I didnt even notice offense and defense on my way up, they just went up naturally as a normal part of playing the way that I did.
<br />
I am sorry your defensive skills suck.  I DID offer advice on how to raise them to the original poster.  I offered the other comments because I get sick and tired of e bayed or power leveled folks coming here and asking how to raise skills that are weak because of the way they leveled.  65 is important.  a 65 Bard with a defense and offense skill 10 can still contribute to raids and groups, or solo.  But they lack something that a bard who has mainly grouped his way to 65 has.
<br />
What matters I guess, is that you have fun playing the game, as long as you dont cause others grief in game with your playing style, it's all good man.  If you have fun playing with a bard lacking 200 points of defensive skills, more power to ya!  If you think it makes sense to get to 65 in 10 days played, then run around for another 3 days finding exploits or tricks to raise all those skills, more power to ya again.  In the end, you might have a a toon who, skill for skill, has the same abilities as a bard with 100 days played, and you have only played 15.  More power to ya!  Have fun, that's all that matters.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
